        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 1:30PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 130 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles north of Rutherfordton, moving southwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Thermal City and Union Mills.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
